<p><b>Tony Clifton</b> is a fictitious character created and often played by stand up comedian <a href="Andy_Kaufman" title="Andy Kaufman">Andy Kaufman</a> in the late 1970s. Characteristic of the many elaborate hoaxes and practical jokes Kaufman concocted, Clifton was not exclusively played by Kaufman—others, mainly <a href="Bob_Zmuda" title="Bob Zmuda">Bob Zmuda</a>, stepped into the role on occasion—enabling Kaufman and his accomplices to create an air of confusion as to whether Clifton was a real person or not.</p>
